        "contact": {
          "email": "imdbot@iamidiotareyoutoo.com"
        },
        "description": "Free Movie DB: The Free Movie Database API. The FM-DB API is a RESTful web service to obtain movie informations. All content and images on the site are contributed and maintained by our users. No API keys or Web Scrapping techniques are used in the generation of any responses by this API.",
        "license": {
          "name": "GNU Affero General Public License 3.0",
          "url": "https://github.com/TelegramPlayGround/Unofficial-IMDb-API/raw/main/LICENSE"
        },
        "servers": [
          {
            "url": "https://imdb.iamidiotareyoutoo.com"
          }
        ],
        "termsOfService": "/legal",
        "title": "Free Movie DB - The Free Movie Database API",
        "version": "0.3.1",
        "tagline": "Search movie, TV, and Spider-Man title data through a community-maintained Free Movie DB endpoint",
        "homepage": "https://imdb.iamidiotareyoutoo.com",
        "docs_url": "https://imdb.iamidiotareyoutoo.com/docs/index.html",
        "license_short": "GNU Affero General Public License 3.0 (AGPL-3.0)",
        "license_md": "- Released under the **GNU Affero General Public License 3.0 (AGPL-3.0)**.\n- Network-deployed derivative works must also offer their source under AGPL-3.0.\n- The project explicitly states it is **not endorsed by or affiliated with IMDb.com**.\n- Content and images are contributed and maintained by users; verify any reuse against AGPL terms.",
        "about_md": "[Free Movie DB (FM-DB)](https://imdb.iamidiotareyoutoo.com) is a community-maintained RESTful service that exposes movie and television metadata, including the Spider-Man movie catalogue used by the [freepublicapis.com listing](https://freepublicapis.com/spider-man-movies-api). The project describes itself as the \"Free Movie Database API\" and states that no API keys or web-scraping techniques are required to access responses.\n\nWhat you get from the API:\n- Title search (e.g. `GET /search?q=Spiderman`) returning movies, shows, and related media records.\n- Media metadata such as titles, release years, and cast/actor details.\n- Photo / image references attached to title records.\n- JustWatch-style streaming availability information surfaced alongside title data.\n\nOperational notes: the API is open and unauthenticated, and the freepublicapis.com listing reports **CORS is disabled** for the public endpoint. No official rate limits are published; the project is donation-supported and tracks issues via GitHub.",
        "entity_desc": {
          "justwatch": "Streaming-availability information (in the style of JustWatch) returned alongside title records.",
          "media": "Movie and TV title records — fields such as title, release year, and cast/actor details.",
          "photo": "Image / poster references associated with a media title.",
          "search": "Title lookup endpoint, e.g. `GET /search?q=<query>`, used to find movies and shows by name."
        },
        "auth": false
      },
